                <note rend="inline" type="source">811B.142/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-22">June 22,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received June 22—8:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3723. American interests Far East. Department’s 538, March 6. Legation, Tokyo,
                    telegraphs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Transferred 100,000 yen Manila June 1st representing approximately 50,000
                            pesos. Bessmer, contemplated by Intercroixrouge as its representative
                            Manila, states amount sufficient one month. Querying Swiss regarding
                            unanswered questions Department’s 538.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
